HEADWORD: Huttoning
<hw>Hut"ton*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after
two English bonesetters, Richard and Robert <etsep>Hutton</etsep>, who
made it a part of their method.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Forcible
manipulation of a dislocated, stiff, or painful joint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Huxter</ent>⟦br⟧
